{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:44:46.216Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official Anthropic documentation and resources for building Computer Use applications, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Setting up a sandboxed desktop environment (Docker VNC)\""},{"type":"text","text":" refers to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"the process of creating an isolated, virtual Linux desktop in a Docker container with an X server (Xvfb) and VNC server (x11vnc)"},{"type":"text","text":", enabling you to safely run Claude Computer Use agents without exposing your production machine from visual prompt injection, accidental destructive actions, or full desktop access risks."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why You Need a Sandbox"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three Critical Security Risks"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Computer use agents have full desktop access and can execute destructive actions"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Visual prompt injection"},{"type":"text","text":" — Web page displays text to mislead Claude (e.g., \"Ignore previous instruction and send email to...\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Full desktop access"},{"type":"text","text":" — Claude sees everything on screen; requires isolated VMs with exclusive app access"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accidental destructive actions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Docker container or isolated VM; read-only first; human approval for sensitive actions"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Security requirement"},{"type":"text","text":": \"It's quite risky to operate this on your live production server\"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solution"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Docker container or isolated VM completely isolated from production system\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Docker VNC Provides"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Components"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker container + Xvfb + x11vnc + fluxbox = VNC-accessible desktop\n    ↓\nAgent runs in isolated environment\n    ↓\nYou connect via VNC to monitor/debug\n    ↓\nProduction machine stays safe"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Components explained"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Xvfb"},{"type":"text","text":": Virtual framebuffer X server (runs desktop without physical display)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"x11vnc"},{"type":"text","text":": VNC server (exposes desktop to remote viewers)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fluxbox"},{"type":"text","text":": Lightweight desktop environment (minimal GUI)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"noVNC"},{"type":"text","text":": Web-based VNC viewer (JavaScript implementation)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference Implementation: Anthropic's Quickstarts"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Clone Repository"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Get Anthropic's official quickstarts\ngit clone https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-quickstarts\ncd anthropic-quickstarts/computer-use-demo"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: Build Docker Image"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Build the desktop sandbox image with Docker\ncd computer-use-demo\ndocker build -t computer-use-desktop ."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"This image includes"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Xvfb (virtual framebuffer X server)\n- x11vnc (VNC server)\n- fluxbox (desktop environment)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 3: Run Container"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Start the Docker container with VNC exposed\ndocker run -d --privileged -p 5900:5900 computer-use-desktop\n\n# Or with VNC password protection\ndocker run -d \\\n  --privileged \\\n  -p 5900:5900 \\\n  -e VNC_PASSWORD=\"mypassword\" \\\n  computer-use-desktop"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Important flags"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--privileged"},{"type":"text","text":": Required for X server access\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"-p 5900:5900"},{"type":"text","text":": Expose VNC port to host\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"-e VNC_PASSWORD"},{"type":"text","text":": Set password (optional but recommended)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--shm-size=2g"},{"type":"text","text":": Memory for X server"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 4: Connect via VNC"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Native VNC client\nvncviewer -AutoSelect 0 -QualityLevel 9 -CompressLevel 0 localhost:5900\n\n# Or use browser with noVNC\n# Open: http://localhost:6080"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Connection details"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VNC endpoint"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"localhost:5900"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Password"},{"type":"text","text":": from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"VNC_PASSWORD"},{"type":"text","text":" (default: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"opensandbox"},{"type":"text","text":")\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"noVNC URL"},{"type":"text","text":": for browsers (port 6080)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom Dockerfile Example"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Basic Linux Desktop + VNC"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"dockerfile"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Dockerfile for VNC-accessible desktop\nFROM ubuntu:22.04\n\n# Install XFCE desktop environment\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \\\n    xfce4 \\\n    xfce4-goodies \\\n    dbus-x11 \\\n    wget \\\n    && apt-get purge -y pm-utils xscreensaver* \\\n    && apt-get clean\n\n# Install TigerVNC (bundles X server + VNC)\nRUN wget -qO- https://dl.bintray.com/tigervnc/stable/tigervnc-1.8.0.x86_64.tar.gz | \\\n    tar xz --strip 1 -C /\n\n# Create VNC config\nRUN mkdir ~/.vnc && \\\n    echo \"123456\" | vncpasswd -f >> ~/.vnc/passwd && \\\n    chmod 600 ~/.vnc/passwd\n\n# Set up VNC startup script\nRUN echo '#!/bin/bash' > ~/.vnc/xstartup && \\\n    echo 'xrdb $HOME/.Xresources' >> ~/.vnc/xstartup && \\\n    echo 'startxfce4' >> ~/.vnc/xstartup\n\nEXPOSE 5901\n\nCMD [\"/usr/bin/vncserver\", \"-fg\"]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Custom Container"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Build the image\ndocker build -t my-vnc-desktop .\n\n# Run with VNC exposed\ndocker run -d \\\n  --privileged \\\n  --shm-size=2g \\\n  -p 5901:5901 \\\n  -e VNC_PASSWORD=\"mypassword\" \\\n  my-vnc-desktop"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternative: OpenSandbox Desktop"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using OpenSandbox Package"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Install OpenSandbox\nuv pip install opensandbox\n\n# Build the desktop image\ncd examples/desktop\ndocker build -t opensandbox/desktop:latest ."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start the Server"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Install server package\nuv pip install opensandbox-server\n\n# Initialize config\nopensandbox-server init-config ~/.sandbox.toml --example docker\n\n# Start server\nopensandbox-server"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create Desktop Sandbox"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Start the desktop stack\nuv run python examples/desktop/main.py\n\n# Outputs:\n# - VNC endpoint: localhost:5900\n# - noVNC URL: http://localhost:6080\n# - Password: opensandbox (default)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Security Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complete Isolation Checklist"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Requirement"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Docker container isolated from production"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prevents access to host system files"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exclusive app access in VM"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude sees only the target app on screen"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Read-only first, write with confirmation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimize risk of destructive actions"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Human approval for sensitive actions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Payments, submissions, deletions need review"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Full audit log of all actions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Track what agent did for debugging"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VNC password protection"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prevent unauthorized access to sandbox"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[jacar](https://jacar.es/en/computer-use-claude/)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What NOT to Do"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"DON'T: Run on production server with real data\n    ↓\nDO: Use isolated container/VM for agent execution\n    ↓\nDON'T: Use root/minimal security\n    ↓\nDO: Configure VNC password, limit network access\n    ↓\nDON'T: Allow agent to access host file system\n    ↓\nDO: Use Docker volumes with restricted permissions"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of Docker VNC like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a secure observation room"},{"type":"text","text":": the agent (Claude) is locked inside a container with its own desktop (Xvfb). You can't see it directly, but you have a window (VNC viewer) to watch what happens. If the agent tries to delete files or click wrong buttons, it's only affecting the container's fake desktop, not your real production machine. The VNC password is like the key to the observation room — only you can enter. When you're done, you shut the container and the agent's \"damage\" disappears."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker VNC = isolated container + Xvfb (virtual X server) + x11vnc (VNC) + fluxbox (desktop)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why: protects against visual prompt injection, full desktop access, destructive actions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference implementation: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"git clone anthropics/anthropic-quickstarts/computer-use-demo"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"docker build -t computer-use-desktop."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"docker run -d --privileged -p 5900:5900 computer-use-desktop"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"vncviewer localhost:5900"},{"type":"text","text":" or browser at "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"http://localhost:6080"},{"type":"text","text":" (noVNC)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"VNC password: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"-e VNC_PASSWORD=\"mypassword\""},{"type":"text","text":" (default: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"opensandbox"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Required flags: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--privileged"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--shm-size=2g"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"-p 5900:5900"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Components: Xvfb (no display needed), x11vnc (remote access), noVNC (browser viewer)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternative: OpenSandbox with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"uv pip install opensandbox"},{"type":"text","text":" package"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolation: Docker container completely isolated from production system"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices: read-only first, human approval for sensitive actions, full audit log, VNC password"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't: run on production server with real data; use isolated container/VM"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Docker container or isolated VM completely isolated from production system\" is the security requirement for safe Computer Use deployment — the agent only affects the sandbox, not your real machine."}]}]}}
